In general, a score of 317 is above the average GRE score, which is around 305. However, some competitive programs may require higher scores, while others may place less emphasis on GRE scores and consider other factors such as GPA, letters of recommendation, and work experience.

It's also important to consider the breakdown of your GRE score. Admissions committees often look at both the verbal and quantitative sections, as well as the analytical writing section. If your score is balanced across all sections, it can strengthen your overall application.

Overall, a score of 317 is a solid score, but it's always a good idea to research the specific requirements of the programs you are interested in and to consider all aspects of your application when determining your chances of admission.
